WEBVTT

00:02.635 --> 00:03.969
<i>- ♪ Crashing through</i>
<i>the crowded halls ♪</i>

00:04.037 --> 00:05.705
<i>♪ Dodging girls</i>
<i>like Ping-Pong balls ♪</i>

00:05.772 --> 00:07.240
<i>♪ Just to reach the bathroom</i>
<i>on time ♪</i>

00:07.307 --> 00:08.641
<i>♪ Leaping over laundry piles ♪</i>

00:08.708 --> 00:10.543
<i>♪ Diapers you can smell</i>
<i>for miles ♪</i>

00:10.610 --> 00:13.980
<i>♪ Guy's got to do</i>
<i>what he can to survive ♪</i>

00:14.047 --> 00:15.048
<i>- ♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>

00:15.115 --> 00:16.483
<i>♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>

00:16.549 --> 00:17.650
<i>- ♪ Duck, dodge, push,</i>
<i>and shove ♪</i>

00:17.717 --> 00:19.386
<i>♪ Is how we show our love ♪</i>

00:19.452 --> 00:21.421
<i>- ♪ In the Loud house,</i>
<i>in the Loud house ♪</i>

00:21.488 --> 00:22.922
<i>- ♪ One boy and ten girls ♪</i>

00:22.989 --> 00:24.924
<i>♪ Wouldn't trade it</i>
<i>for the world ♪</i>

00:24.991 --> 00:28.061
<i>- ♪ Loud Loud Loud ♪</i>

00:28.128 --> 00:29.396
{\an8}<i>♪ Loud house ♪</i>

00:29.462 --> 00:30.697
{\an8}- Poo-poo.

00:34.701 --> 00:37.637
<i>[rock music]</i>

00:37.704 --> 00:44.644
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:45.879 --> 00:47.113
{\an1}- Hey, you guys,
don't forget,

00:47.180 --> 00:50.016
{\an1}my golf tournament's
this afternoon.

00:50.083 --> 00:52.152
{\an1}You're all going to be there
to support me, right?

00:52.218 --> 00:54.354
- Fore!
- You better believe it!

00:54.421 --> 00:55.989
- And after that,
you're all coming

00:56.055 --> 00:57.991
to my charity fashion show,
right?

00:58.057 --> 00:59.793
[all speaking at once]

00:59.859 --> 01:02.862
- And after that, don't forget
my grave-digging competition.

01:02.929 --> 01:05.532
[all speaking at once]

01:05.598 --> 01:06.833
{\an1}- 'Inkin!

01:06.900 --> 01:09.736
{\an3}- Shh.

01:09.803 --> 01:11.938
- [giggling]

01:13.840 --> 01:15.375
- [sighs, clears throat]

01:15.442 --> 01:16.676
I know what you're thinking.

01:16.743 --> 01:18.178
"Lincoln, why are you trying

01:18.244 --> 01:20.447
to get out of
all your sisters' activities?"

01:20.513 --> 01:22.449
Well, you don't know my life.

01:22.515 --> 01:25.485
<i>With ten sisters, my calendar's</i>
<i>booked every day with stuff.</i>

01:25.552 --> 01:29.189
<i>I'm supposed to go to rodeos,</i>
<i>pageants, open mic nights.</i>

01:29.255 --> 01:31.724
Once in a while, a guy
just needs some time to himself.

01:31.791 --> 01:34.494
{\an1}- Hey, Lincoln. You're coming to
my softball game today, right?

01:34.561 --> 01:36.696
{\an3}- Dang it.
Should've done a head count.

01:36.763 --> 01:40.633
{\an3}Actually, Lynn, I've got some
important business to attend to.

01:40.700 --> 01:43.570
{\an3}Like Ace Savvy
versus the Card Shark.

01:43.636 --> 01:46.339
{\an1}- Lame. My team has won
our last six games,

01:46.406 --> 01:48.208
{\an1}and you're the only member
of this family

01:48.274 --> 01:49.742
{\an1}who hasn't come out
to support me.

01:49.809 --> 01:52.579
{\an3}- That's because I was
supporting six other sisters

01:52.645 --> 01:53.813
at their things.

01:53.880 --> 01:56.149
{\an3}Sorry, Lynn,
I just can't do it today.

01:56.216 --> 01:58.618
- Sure you won't reconsider?

01:58.685 --> 02:01.020
[crowd cheering]

02:01.087 --> 02:02.322
- Let's do this!

02:02.388 --> 02:03.990
{\an1}- Well, it's a beautiful day
at the park.

02:04.057 --> 02:06.059
Isn't it, Pep?
- Oh, sure it is.

02:06.125 --> 02:07.160
- It's the bottom of the ninth

02:07.227 --> 02:08.627
with the Royal Woods Squirrels

02:08.695 --> 02:09.762
up 3-nothing.

02:09.829 --> 02:10.896
Could this be another shutout

02:10.964 --> 02:12.799
for star pitcher Lynn Loud?

02:12.866 --> 02:15.502
[cheers and applause]

02:15.568 --> 02:16.903
- Go, Lynn!

02:16.970 --> 02:20.373
- Loud is performing
her signature good luck rituals.

02:21.474 --> 02:23.576
- Hutta-hut! Hutta-hut!
Hutta-hut!

02:23.643 --> 02:25.345
{\an1}- Hey, Pep, you believe
there's anything

02:25.411 --> 02:26.946
to these kinds of superstitions?

02:27.013 --> 02:28.381
- I don't know.

02:28.448 --> 02:31.551
- Well, here's the windup,
and the pitch.

02:31.618 --> 02:33.853
Ooh, looks like
the softball gods

02:33.920 --> 02:36.289
did not love that cossack dance.

02:36.356 --> 02:38.057
[crowd exclaiming]

02:38.124 --> 02:41.060
<i>[exciting music]</i>

02:41.127 --> 02:42.362
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:42.428 --> 02:44.063
Hated that cossack dance.

02:44.130 --> 02:45.131
[crowd booing]

02:45.198 --> 02:47.400
- Don't worry about it, sis!

02:48.668 --> 02:51.137
{\an3}Hey, sis.
I'm really sorry you lost.

02:51.204 --> 02:52.839
- [gasps]
- Hey.

02:52.906 --> 02:53.940
- Stay back.

02:54.007 --> 02:56.042
You're bad luck.

02:56.109 --> 02:57.310
- What are you talking about?

02:57.377 --> 02:59.579
{\an1}- My team has been dominating
all season,

02:59.646 --> 03:02.382
{\an1}then the one time you show up,
we lose.

03:02.448 --> 03:03.616
- That's ridiculous.

03:03.683 --> 03:04.617
I'm not bad luck.

03:04.684 --> 03:06.019
- Yeah-huh you are,

03:06.085 --> 03:09.022
{\an1}which is why I'm banning you
from all future games.

03:09.088 --> 03:10.056
{\an1}Now scram!

03:10.123 --> 03:11.090
I have to make things right

03:11.157 --> 03:12.625
with the softball gods.

03:12.692 --> 03:13.993
Hutta-hut! Hutta-hut!

03:14.060 --> 03:15.895
{\an1}Hutta-hut!

03:15.962 --> 03:18.831
{\an3}- Lincoln, are you coming
to my charity fashion show?

03:18.898 --> 03:20.099
It's for a great cause:

03:20.166 --> 03:21.768
oysters without pearls.

03:21.834 --> 03:22.802
- Leni, no!

03:22.869 --> 03:24.003
He'll ruin your fashion show

03:24.070 --> 03:25.738
just like he ruined
my winning streak.

03:25.805 --> 03:27.140
He's bad luck!

03:27.206 --> 03:28.374
- Oh, come on, Lynn,

03:28.441 --> 03:30.877
that is absolutely...

03:30.944 --> 03:32.612
true.

03:32.679 --> 03:34.714
I think I may be
onto something here.

03:34.781 --> 03:37.250
Leni, I'd love to go
to your fashion show,

03:37.317 --> 03:39.252
but I'd hate for my bad luck
to make you trip,

03:39.319 --> 03:41.454
or jam a zipper,
or break a heel.

03:41.521 --> 03:43.022
- [gasps]
The horror!

03:43.089 --> 03:44.824
Maybe you should
sit this one out.

03:44.891 --> 03:47.193
- I'll be there in spirit.

03:47.260 --> 03:48.995
<i>- Next on "Arggh!"...</i>

03:49.062 --> 03:50.029
- [exclaims]

03:50.096 --> 03:51.030
[both grunting]

03:51.097 --> 03:52.031
Hey, Linc, you coming

03:52.098 --> 03:54.300
to my alligator-wrestling match?

03:54.367 --> 03:56.002
- Don't invite Lincoln.

03:56.069 --> 03:57.403
{\an3}He could make
your alligator trip,

03:57.470 --> 03:59.939
{\an3}or jam its zipper,
or break a heel.

04:00.006 --> 04:02.976
- What?
- He's bad luck.

04:03.042 --> 04:04.377
- I can't deny it.

04:04.444 --> 04:06.579
{\an3}- Uh, maybe you shouldn't come
after all.

04:06.646 --> 04:08.548
{\an3}I'm wrestli''
my first 200-pounder,

04:08.615 --> 04:10.483
and I can't take any chances.

04:11.818 --> 04:13.620
{\an3}- Sure, Lola,
I'll come to your pageant.

04:13.686 --> 04:16.555
{\an3}I just hope my bad luck
doesn't make your hair go flat.

04:16.623 --> 04:19.492
{\an1}- [gasps]
Get away from me!

04:19.559 --> 04:21.861
{\an1}- I'd love to attend
your performance.

04:21.928 --> 04:23.229
I'm just afraid my bad luck

04:23.296 --> 04:25.264
{\an1}might cause
a clown car collision.

04:25.331 --> 04:28.034
{\an3}- [gasps]
That would put a dent in things!

04:28.101 --> 04:29.535
{\an3}[laughing]
Get it?

04:29.602 --> 04:31.638
But seriously, don't come.

04:32.605 --> 04:34.240
- Oh, Lily, I sure would like

04:34.307 --> 04:35.341
to come to your playdate,

04:35.408 --> 04:36.776
but I'd hate for my bad luck

04:36.843 --> 04:37.944
to cause a boo-boo.

04:38.011 --> 04:39.579
- [blowing raspberry]

04:39.646 --> 04:40.747
{\an3}- [scoffs]

04:40.813 --> 04:42.882
{\an3}There's no such thing
as bad luck.

04:42.949 --> 04:44.183
There's only science.

04:44.250 --> 04:45.318
All else is hooey.

04:45.385 --> 04:46.786
- Lisa literally has a point.

04:46.853 --> 04:48.588
{\an1}You're coming to my tournament,
Lincoln.

04:48.655 --> 04:50.490
This family supports each other.

04:50.556 --> 04:52.125
- You're right, I'm being silly.

04:52.191 --> 04:53.826
Let me get those for you.

04:53.893 --> 04:55.028
Whoa!

04:55.094 --> 04:57.830
Whoa, whoa!

04:57.897 --> 04:59.899
[clattering]

04:59.966 --> 05:00.967
Whoops.

05:01.034 --> 05:02.769
- [gasps]
My sand wedge!

05:02.835 --> 05:04.137
You are bad luck.

05:04.203 --> 05:06.406
You are literally uninvited
to my tournament.

05:06.472 --> 05:08.441
{\an3}- I retract
my earlier statement.

05:08.508 --> 05:10.743
Back, ye cursed wretch!

05:10.810 --> 05:12.545
{\an3}And don't even think
about attending

05:12.612 --> 05:15.214
my lecture series
on thermodynamics.

05:15.281 --> 05:17.917
{\an1}- Aw, man.

05:17.984 --> 05:20.753
- Come on, guys, it's time
for my gator-wrestling match.

05:20.820 --> 05:22.121
[excited chatter]

05:22.188 --> 05:23.423
[door closes]

05:23.489 --> 05:25.324
- So sorry to miss it all.

05:25.391 --> 05:27.093
<i>[rock music]</i>

05:27.160 --> 05:28.161
Who's unlucky?

05:28.227 --> 05:29.395
I'm unlucky.

05:29.462 --> 05:31.431
Who's unlucky?
I'm unlucky.

05:31.497 --> 05:32.765
Tough break, Card Shark.

05:32.832 --> 05:35.568
Looks like Ace Savvy
just called your bluff.

05:35.635 --> 05:36.936
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:37.003 --> 05:38.638
[burps]

05:38.705 --> 05:39.972
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:40.039 --> 05:41.941
I got to say, being bad luck

05:42.008 --> 05:44.210
turned out to be pretty good.

05:47.780 --> 05:48.981
What the--

05:49.048 --> 05:51.417
why is my breakfast
on the coffee table?

05:51.484 --> 05:53.786
- Oh, sorry, sweetheart,
but would you mind

05:53.853 --> 05:55.922
eating breakfast
in the living room today?

05:55.988 --> 05:58.191
- I've got a big presentation,
and your mother's got

05:58.257 --> 05:59.726
back-to-back
root canal patients.

05:59.792 --> 06:02.495
We--we can't risk your bad luck
spreading to us.

06:03.963 --> 06:06.499
- Just another perk
of the bad luck life.

06:06.566 --> 06:10.069
Now I can play video games
while I eat.

06:10.136 --> 06:12.972
- Come on, kids, the movie
starts in half an hour!

06:13.039 --> 06:15.408
- This is gonna be, like,
the best movie ever!

06:15.475 --> 06:16.876
- So awesome!

06:16.943 --> 06:18.111
- Dibs on holding the popcorn.

06:18.177 --> 06:19.412
{\an3}- [yells]

06:19.479 --> 06:20.780
- Whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa.

06:20.847 --> 06:22.548
Not so fast, son.
I wish you could come,

06:22.615 --> 06:24.617
but with your bad luck,
who knows what could go wrong?

06:24.684 --> 06:26.552
- The movie could sell out!

06:26.619 --> 06:29.155
- I could get stuck behind
some lady with a beehive.

06:29.222 --> 06:32.325
- Someone could get scalded
with molten butter.

06:32.391 --> 06:34.026
{\an1}- [gasps]
I didn't even think of that one.

06:34.093 --> 06:35.094
Sorry, kiddo.

06:35.161 --> 06:37.096
- Oh...no problem.

06:37.163 --> 06:38.231
You guys have fun.

06:38.297 --> 06:39.499
- Don't worry, I'll tell you

06:39.565 --> 06:41.701
how the movie ends.

06:41.768 --> 06:43.369
- Eh, what's missing one movie

06:43.436 --> 06:47.173
when it means having
more awesome me time?

06:47.240 --> 06:49.108
<i>[gloomy rock music]</i>

06:49.175 --> 06:50.243
Who is unlucky?

06:50.309 --> 06:51.477
I'm unlucky.

06:51.544 --> 06:54.046
Who's unlucky?
I'm unlucky.

06:54.113 --> 06:55.715
Take that, Wild Card Willie.

06:55.782 --> 06:58.618
Ace Savvy just dealt you
some justice.

07:02.955 --> 07:04.090
[tires screeching]

07:04.157 --> 07:07.293
[excited chatter]

07:08.928 --> 07:10.797
[sighs]

07:15.501 --> 07:16.769
"Sorry, Lincoln,

07:16.836 --> 07:18.538
"but you can't
sleep here tonight.

07:18.604 --> 07:20.173
We just can't risk it"?

07:20.239 --> 07:21.674
Are you kidding me?

07:21.741 --> 07:22.708
all: No!

07:24.110 --> 07:26.179
- Hey, buddy, think I could
bunk here for the night?

07:26.245 --> 07:27.180
[dog growling]

07:27.246 --> 07:28.714
<i>Et tu,</i> Charles?

07:30.216 --> 07:35.755
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:44.030 --> 07:47.033
Guys? I think you
accidentally locked me out.

07:48.467 --> 07:50.536
- Kids, we've got
a special treat for you.

07:50.603 --> 07:53.840
Since your father's presentation
went so well...

07:53.906 --> 07:55.741
- And your mother's
root canals too.

07:55.808 --> 07:58.878
- We thought we'd celebrate with
a trip to the beach tomorrow.

07:58.945 --> 08:00.913
[all cheering]

08:00.980 --> 08:02.715
{\an1}- We're going
to the beach tomorrow?

08:02.782 --> 08:04.417
- Ooh, gosh, sorry, son.
Not you.

08:04.483 --> 08:06.118
Someone could get attacked
by a shark.

08:06.185 --> 08:08.120
- Or caught in a riptide.

08:08.187 --> 08:09.522
- Or stung by a jellyfish.

08:09.589 --> 08:10.790
- [gasps]
If that happens,

08:10.857 --> 08:12.658
I call peeing on the wound!

08:12.725 --> 08:15.294
{\an1}- Come on, you guys,
be reasonable.

08:15.361 --> 08:17.363
- You're bad luck, Lincoln.

08:17.430 --> 08:19.465
You can't come!

08:20.566 --> 08:22.902
- I guess I brought this
on myself.

08:25.238 --> 08:26.939
Attention, Loud family!

08:27.006 --> 08:28.074
[feedback screeching]

08:28.140 --> 08:29.742
I have a confession to make.

08:33.412 --> 08:35.347
Contrary to popular belief,

08:35.414 --> 08:36.682
I am not bad luck.

08:36.749 --> 08:38.451
I just let you guys believe that

08:38.517 --> 08:40.486
so I could get out of going
to your stuff.

08:40.553 --> 08:42.421
It was a really selfish
thing to do.

08:42.488 --> 08:44.222
We all need to support
each other.

08:44.290 --> 08:45.558
I'm really sorry.

08:45.625 --> 08:47.660
- Nice confession, Loud!

08:47.727 --> 08:49.395
- If you're not bad luck,

08:49.462 --> 08:51.430
{\an1}then how come
after I banned you,

08:51.497 --> 08:53.032
{\an1}my team won
our doubleheader,

08:53.099 --> 08:55.001
{\an1}and now we're going
to the playoffs?

08:55.067 --> 08:55.935
{\an1}Huh?

08:56.002 --> 08:57.770
- She's got you there, Loud!

08:57.837 --> 08:59.639
- Could you just please
go back inside?

08:59.705 --> 09:01.274
- Sorry, buddy!
- I'm sorry, honey.

09:01.340 --> 09:02.742
- We'll write!
- Lynn's right, you're bad luck.

09:02.808 --> 09:05.478
- Step farther away
from the house.

09:05.544 --> 09:08.014
- Ugh, Lynn
and her superstitions!

09:08.080 --> 09:10.716
As long as she thinks
I'm bad luck, I'm doomed.

09:10.783 --> 09:13.519
I have to find a way
to prove her wrong.

09:13.586 --> 09:15.354
Dang squirrel!

09:15.421 --> 09:16.856
Squirrel!

09:16.923 --> 09:18.190
Hmm.

09:18.257 --> 09:20.192
- Go, Lynn!

09:20.259 --> 09:21.928
[cheers and applause]

09:21.994 --> 09:23.763
- What's with
that squirrel today?

09:23.829 --> 09:26.065
His choreography is so dated.

09:26.132 --> 09:28.567
- Hey, man!
You try dancing in this heat.

09:28.634 --> 09:31.404
My plan is simple:
I watch the game in disguise,

09:31.470 --> 09:32.805
and when the Squirrels win,

09:32.872 --> 09:35.007
everyone will see
I'm not bad luck.

09:36.375 --> 09:37.677
- Talk about bad luck.

09:37.743 --> 09:39.478
Everything is going wrong
for the Squirrels today.

09:39.545 --> 09:40.579
What do you think, Pep?

09:40.646 --> 09:41.914
- I think I've wasted my life.

09:41.981 --> 09:44.116
{\an1}- Just look at
our poor Squirrels!

09:45.184 --> 09:47.453
[crowd murmuring]

09:47.520 --> 09:48.521
[both grunting]

09:48.587 --> 09:55.728
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:55.795 --> 09:56.796
{\an1}- Yowza.

09:56.862 --> 09:58.264
{\an1}Two outs in the bottom
of the ninth,

09:58.331 --> 09:59.498
and the bases are loaded.

09:59.565 --> 10:00.866
Lynn Loud steps up to the plate,

10:00.933 --> 10:02.802
but with the luck
she's been having today,

10:02.868 --> 10:05.604
the Squirrels are looking
a whole lot like roadkill.

10:05.671 --> 10:07.139
- Way harsh, dude!

10:07.206 --> 10:08.774
{\an1}- I think you're
rubbing off on me, Pep.

10:08.841 --> 10:10.710
{\an3}- Oh, I have that effect
on people.

10:10.776 --> 10:13.045
- The windup, the pitch.

10:13.112 --> 10:14.880
- Strike one!

10:16.816 --> 10:20.052
- Lynn's right, I am bad luck.

10:20.119 --> 10:21.754
- Strike two!

10:21.821 --> 10:24.056
- Maybe I can move
into Lisa's fallout shelter.

10:24.123 --> 10:27.293
Lead walls will keep my bad luck
from affecting anyone.

10:27.360 --> 10:28.694
- And the pitch!

10:28.761 --> 10:30.663
It's going, it's going,

10:30.730 --> 10:31.864
it's gone!

10:31.931 --> 10:33.699
Lynn Loud hits a grand slam!

10:33.766 --> 10:36.068
Squirrels win!
Squirrels win!

10:36.135 --> 10:37.737
[cheers and applause]

10:37.803 --> 10:40.339
Squirrels win!
Squirrels win!

10:40.406 --> 10:42.908
[cheers and applause]

10:42.975 --> 10:45.611
- Congratulations!
- You rocked it, Lynn-sanity!

10:45.678 --> 10:47.680
- Um, do you mind, fur ball?

10:47.747 --> 10:49.248
This is a family moment.

10:49.315 --> 10:50.249
- Guys, it's me.

10:50.316 --> 10:51.417
I was here the whole time.

10:51.484 --> 10:52.418
This proves it.

10:52.485 --> 10:53.519
I'm not bad luck.

10:53.586 --> 10:55.521
- Oh, my gosh, you're right.

10:55.588 --> 10:58.324
{\an1}Wow, Lincoln.
I'm really sorry.

10:58.391 --> 10:59.525
- Sorry, Lincoln.

10:59.592 --> 11:01.694
- Sorry we sold
all your furniture.

11:01.761 --> 11:04.363
- Wait, what?

11:04.430 --> 11:06.966
Well, my family doesn't think
I'm bad luck anymore.

11:07.033 --> 11:08.901
In fact, now they think
I'm good luck.

11:08.968 --> 11:10.870
{\an3}- Hey, Lincoln,
put the head back on

11:10.936 --> 11:13.139
{\an3}before we get stung
by a jellyfish!

11:13.205 --> 11:14.306
- But unfortunately,

11:14.373 --> 11:16.642
only when I'm in
the squirrel suit.

11:22.181 --> 11:25.117
<i>[whimsical music]</i>

11:25.184 --> 11:30.122
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:30.189 --> 11:31.757
[school bell ringing]
<i>- Okay, class.</i>

11:31.824 --> 11:34.827
Tomorrow we're wrapping up
our biology studies

11:34.894 --> 11:36.462
with a special project.

11:36.529 --> 11:38.431
We'll be dissecting...

11:38.497 --> 11:39.799
frogs!

11:39.865 --> 11:41.834
[all exclaiming]

11:41.901 --> 11:43.936
- Get ready to jump in.

11:44.003 --> 11:47.139
[laughing]

11:48.140 --> 11:50.042
Really? No one?

11:50.109 --> 11:51.644
- Dissecting frogs?

11:51.710 --> 11:52.645
That sounds...

11:52.711 --> 11:53.646
- Horrible!

11:53.712 --> 11:55.047
You can't do that.

11:55.114 --> 11:56.082
- They're just frogs, Lana.

11:56.148 --> 11:57.383
What's the big deal?

11:57.450 --> 11:59.018
- I'll show you
what the big deal is.

11:59.085 --> 12:00.820
{\an1}- Ow, ow!

12:00.886 --> 12:04.090
{\an3}- Watch this movie I made
about Hops.

12:04.156 --> 12:05.524
{\an3}- [croaks]

12:06.459 --> 12:09.228
{\an8}<i>- "Hops: A Life in Leaps."</i>

12:09.295 --> 12:11.063
<i>I'll never forget the day</i>

12:11.130 --> 12:13.866
<i>I met my future best friend.</i>

12:15.668 --> 12:16.802
{\an1}- [croaks]

12:16.869 --> 12:17.803
{\an3}- [laughs]

12:17.870 --> 12:19.271
You're the best froggy.

12:19.338 --> 12:20.439
Well, I got to go.

12:20.506 --> 12:22.108
Dad's making meatloaf tonight.

12:22.174 --> 12:23.809
Thanks for the fun day.

12:26.011 --> 12:28.347
<i>[somber string music]</i>

12:28.414 --> 12:31.283
{\an3}Aww, you're lonely,
aren't you, little guy?

12:31.350 --> 12:33.786
{\an3}Would you like to come home
and live with me?

12:34.854 --> 12:37.790
<i>[cheerful piano music]</i>

12:37.857 --> 12:39.125
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:39.191 --> 12:40.926
I'm gonna name you Hops!

12:40.993 --> 12:41.927
- [croaks]

12:41.994 --> 12:43.062
<i>- Since that day,</i>

12:43.129 --> 12:45.030
<i>we've been pretty inseparable.</i>

12:45.097 --> 12:46.899
<i>We eat all our meals together.</i>

12:46.966 --> 12:49.135
<i>Hops likes his crickets</i>
<i>chocolate-covered,</i>

12:49.201 --> 12:50.336
<i>but I like mine plain.</i>

12:50.402 --> 12:51.837
<i>We play together.</i>

12:51.904 --> 12:54.440
<i>We even get our school photos</i>
<i>taken together.</i>

12:54.507 --> 12:56.642
- All right, kid, smile.

12:56.709 --> 12:58.811
Three, two, one.

12:58.878 --> 13:01.247
Cheese.

13:01.313 --> 13:03.816
- Nighty night, buddy.

13:03.883 --> 13:05.317
- [croaks]

13:05.384 --> 13:07.219
<i>- I can't imagine</i>
<i>what life would be like</i>

13:07.286 --> 13:09.655
<i>without my best friend Hops.</i>

13:09.722 --> 13:12.658
{\an1}[snoring]

13:13.893 --> 13:19.198
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:19.265 --> 13:23.969
- That was the most beautiful
thing I've ever seen.

13:24.036 --> 13:25.070
- You see, Lincoln?

13:25.137 --> 13:27.006
Frogs are cooler on the outside

13:27.072 --> 13:28.541
than they are on the inside.

13:28.607 --> 13:30.743
So please don't dissect them.

13:30.809 --> 13:33.345
{\an1}- I won't,
and neither will anyone else.

13:33.412 --> 13:34.513
- What do you mean?

13:34.580 --> 13:37.750
{\an1}- We're going
on a rescue mission.

13:37.816 --> 13:40.186
- Don't forget Hops.

13:40.252 --> 13:41.220
<i>- All right, class,</i>

13:41.287 --> 13:42.688
<i>when we return from lunch</i>

13:42.755 --> 13:47.193
we'll leap into
our frog dissecting.

13:47.259 --> 13:48.327
Come on, people.

13:48.394 --> 13:50.396
I'm giving you comedy gold here.

13:50.462 --> 13:52.932
[school bell rings]

13:54.233 --> 13:57.336
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

13:57.403 --> 13:59.138
- Lana, where are you?

13:59.205 --> 14:00.406
{\an1}[gasps]
Oh.

14:00.472 --> 14:01.540
Good hiding place.

14:01.607 --> 14:02.775
- What are you talking about?

14:02.841 --> 14:04.577
{\an3}Hops and I were just
eating lunch.

14:04.643 --> 14:05.578
{\an3}[burps]

14:05.644 --> 14:06.779
- [burps]

14:06.845 --> 14:07.980
- Let's go.

14:08.047 --> 14:13.219
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:13.285 --> 14:14.687
- We have a problem.

14:14.753 --> 14:16.355
It's a surface mounted deadbolt

14:16.422 --> 14:18.224
{\an1}with a tumbler
locking mechanism.

14:18.290 --> 14:20.192
- In English, please?

14:20.259 --> 14:22.294
{\an1}- We'll have to find
another way in.

14:22.361 --> 14:29.501
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:32.137 --> 14:33.272
- [straining]

14:33.339 --> 14:36.242
{\an8}<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:36.308 --> 14:37.576
{\an8}- [gasps]
Principal Huggins?

14:37.643 --> 14:39.378
{\an8}Wrong room.
Wrong room!

14:39.445 --> 14:41.747
{\an8}[straining]

14:41.814 --> 14:48.754
{\an8}<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:50.889 --> 14:51.824
{\an3}[exhales]

14:51.890 --> 14:53.425
Good job, Hops.

14:54.927 --> 14:57.396
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:57.463 --> 14:59.131
- What's up, frog-ays?

14:59.198 --> 15:01.166
We're here to rescue you.

15:01.233 --> 15:02.268
- [grunting]

15:02.334 --> 15:03.902
{\an1}Let's go.

15:03.969 --> 15:04.903
[doorknob rattling]

15:04.970 --> 15:05.904
[both gulp]

15:07.006 --> 15:09.308
- [gasps]
My frogs!

15:10.609 --> 15:11.977
[school bell ringing]
Principal Huggins!

15:12.044 --> 15:13.646
Principal Huggins!

15:14.980 --> 15:17.816
- Whoa, that open window decoy
was brilliant.

15:17.883 --> 15:21.053
- What do you think,
this is my first animal rescue?

15:21.120 --> 15:25.391
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:25.457 --> 15:27.660
- Be free, my amphibian friends,

15:27.726 --> 15:30.362
{\an1}be free!

15:30.429 --> 15:31.864
- [croaking]

15:33.399 --> 15:35.034
- Good luck, frog-ays!

15:35.100 --> 15:36.835
Have a nice life.

15:36.902 --> 15:37.836
- [croaks]

15:37.903 --> 15:40.706
[birds screeching]

15:40.773 --> 15:44.443
{\an1}- Uh, you guys might want
to get moving.

15:45.611 --> 15:47.313
- Seriously, guys, go!

15:47.379 --> 15:48.714
- [hisses]

15:48.781 --> 15:50.683
{\an1}- Do you want to be
today's lunch special?

15:50.749 --> 15:52.951
{\an1}Move!
Why aren't they moving?

15:53.018 --> 15:55.988
{\an3}- Maybe they don't know
how to survive in the wild.

15:56.055 --> 15:57.089
{\an3}Hey, you!

15:57.156 --> 15:59.391
{\an3}Not cool!

15:59.458 --> 16:01.593
Lincoln, we can't
leave them here.

16:01.660 --> 16:03.295
{\an3}- You're right.
We'll take them home

16:03.362 --> 16:05.631
{\an3}till we can think of
a better plan.

16:07.099 --> 16:08.901
- Don't even think about it!

16:11.036 --> 16:12.004
<i>- They'll be safe here.</i>

16:12.071 --> 16:13.105
Come on, we got to go.

16:13.172 --> 16:14.707
Lunch hour's almost up.

16:15.574 --> 16:16.809
- All right, Hops.

16:16.875 --> 16:18.944
Keep an eye on them
till we get back.

16:21.680 --> 16:22.948
- Whew!

16:23.015 --> 16:24.683
- Good afternoon, class.

16:24.750 --> 16:26.719
Mrs. Johnson has informed me

16:26.785 --> 16:30.055
that some frogs
have gone missing.

16:30.122 --> 16:32.991
Does anyone know anything
about that?

16:34.460 --> 16:36.762
Well, I've been in this racket
for quite a while,

16:36.829 --> 16:38.330
and I think I know
what happened.

16:38.397 --> 16:40.366
One of you thought
you'd be a hero

16:40.432 --> 16:41.767
and rescue the poor creatures,

16:41.834 --> 16:43.769
and the frogs
would be so grateful

16:43.836 --> 16:45.437
they'd put up a statue of you.

16:45.504 --> 16:49.274
So who is the frog hero?

16:49.341 --> 16:50.909
Is it you?

16:50.976 --> 16:51.944
Ribbit, ribbit.

16:52.010 --> 16:52.945
- [laughs nervously]

16:53.011 --> 16:54.546
Uh, uh, not me, sir.

16:54.613 --> 16:56.482
I'm no hero.

16:56.548 --> 16:58.650
- Okay.
No one wants to confess.

16:58.717 --> 17:01.720
I guess we can
just let it slide.

17:01.787 --> 17:02.755
Not!

17:02.821 --> 17:04.757
I'll find the frog hero myself

17:04.823 --> 17:08.127
by searching each of your houses
after school.

17:08.193 --> 17:09.127
So get ready.

17:09.194 --> 17:11.363
Huggins is coming.

17:11.430 --> 17:12.765
- [gulps]

17:14.266 --> 17:16.101
Lana!

17:16.167 --> 17:19.037
Wait, it's her after school
snack time.

17:20.406 --> 17:21.973
Lana!

17:22.040 --> 17:23.474
{\an1}- Hey, Lincoln.
Gum?

17:23.541 --> 17:24.510
{\an3}- Ugh!

17:24.576 --> 17:25.676
Come on, we got to get home

17:25.743 --> 17:27.846
and hide those frogs, stat!

17:30.916 --> 17:34.086
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:34.153 --> 17:35.120
[knocking at door]

17:35.187 --> 17:36.555
Open up, Dombrowski.

17:36.622 --> 17:39.591
Frog inspection.

17:39.658 --> 17:41.460
{\an3}- We'll just hide the frogs
in the garage,

17:41.527 --> 17:44.129
{\an3}easy peasy.

17:44.196 --> 17:46.165
- Not so easy peasy.

17:46.231 --> 17:48.667
[frogs croaking]

17:48.734 --> 17:51.503
Hops, how'd the frogs get out?

17:51.570 --> 17:54.506
<i>[rock music]</i>

17:54.573 --> 17:56.241
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:56.308 --> 17:57.409
{\an1}- [croaks]

17:57.476 --> 17:58.944
[horn honking]

17:59.011 --> 18:00.646
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:00.712 --> 18:02.014
- 10 down, 40 to go.

18:02.080 --> 18:03.515
<i>[pounding at door]</i>
<i>- Open up, Loud.</i>

18:03.582 --> 18:05.217
<i>Frog inspection!</i>

18:06.485 --> 18:09.721
Good afternoon, children.

18:09.788 --> 18:11.757
{\an1}Well, I don't see
any frogs here.

18:11.824 --> 18:14.693
I guess I'll just be on my way.

18:14.760 --> 18:16.028
{\an1}Not!

18:16.094 --> 18:21.233
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:21.300 --> 18:22.267
- [exclaims]

18:22.334 --> 18:23.836
Let me take your coat.

18:23.902 --> 18:25.170
{\an1}- Ah!

18:25.237 --> 18:26.572
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:26.638 --> 18:28.574
{\an1}Yes, just put that down
anywhere,

18:28.640 --> 18:31.076
why don't you?

18:31.143 --> 18:32.311
{\an1}Ugh.

18:32.377 --> 18:35.414
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:35.481 --> 18:36.982
{\an1}- [croaks]

18:37.049 --> 18:39.985
{\an1}- Uh, I didn't want the glare
to hurt your eyeballs, sir.

18:40.052 --> 18:40.986
[glass shattering]

18:41.053 --> 18:41.987
- What was that?

18:49.328 --> 18:51.597
You two seem a bit nervous.

18:51.663 --> 18:53.098
- [muffled]
Not at all.

18:56.101 --> 18:57.469
Mmm. Protein.

18:57.536 --> 18:58.670
[chuckles]

19:00.305 --> 19:06.144
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:06.211 --> 19:07.145
- Sorry, sir.

19:07.212 --> 19:08.747
You had some schmutz on you.

19:08.814 --> 19:10.916
Here, let me get you a towel.

19:13.385 --> 19:14.319
- Stop that!

19:14.386 --> 19:15.954
[distant thud]

19:16.021 --> 19:16.922
{\an1}Hmm.

19:16.989 --> 19:19.258
Maybe I'll go check upstairs.

19:19.324 --> 19:24.129
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:24.196 --> 19:25.197
- Wet willie!

19:25.264 --> 19:27.900
{\an1}Uh, just trying
to lighten the mood.

19:29.167 --> 19:30.402
- What's this room?

19:30.469 --> 19:31.970
- That's Lucy
and Lynn's bedroom,

19:32.037 --> 19:33.272
but I wouldn't go in there.

19:33.338 --> 19:34.673
Lucy's kind of spooky.

19:34.740 --> 19:37.142
{\an1}- If you think I'm afraid
of a little--

19:37.209 --> 19:39.545
[screaming]

19:39.611 --> 19:41.046
That room looks clear.

19:41.113 --> 19:43.048
[clears throat]

19:43.115 --> 19:44.349
What's this room?

19:44.416 --> 19:45.918
- That's Lori
and Leni's bedroom,

19:45.984 --> 19:47.219
but I wouldn't go in there.

19:47.286 --> 19:49.755
They have a pretty intense
security system.

19:49.821 --> 19:51.490
- I'll take my chances.

19:51.557 --> 19:52.958
[electricity crackling]

19:55.794 --> 19:57.696
Well, upstairs looks clear.

19:57.763 --> 19:59.765
I need to use your restroom.

20:01.800 --> 20:03.635
I usually do this alone.

20:03.702 --> 20:05.137
{\an1}- Oh, right.
Sure.

20:05.203 --> 20:07.839
{\an1}Uh, I'm just gonna...
check the toilet.

20:07.906 --> 20:10.275
Got to make sure I didn't
leave anything in there.

20:12.244 --> 20:13.579
You're good to go.

20:16.648 --> 20:18.684
<i>[rock music]</i>

20:18.750 --> 20:20.152
- [exclaims]

20:20.218 --> 20:21.453
- [croaks]

20:21.520 --> 20:23.155
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:23.221 --> 20:24.690
- [panting]

20:24.756 --> 20:27.426
- Well, it appears your house
is frog-free,

20:27.492 --> 20:29.094
so I'll be on my way.

20:29.161 --> 20:30.395
- Good luck, sir.

20:30.462 --> 20:31.830
Keep fighting the good fight.

20:31.897 --> 20:33.899
- I'll just grab your--coat?

20:33.966 --> 20:36.535
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

20:36.602 --> 20:37.803
{\an1}[gasps]

20:37.869 --> 20:40.272
- I'll grab my own coat.

20:40.339 --> 20:42.941
[both gasp]

20:43.008 --> 20:45.010
- What is wrong with you two?

20:45.077 --> 20:47.913
- Nothin'.
Drive safe.

20:49.581 --> 20:50.515
- What the--whoa!

20:50.582 --> 20:51.516
[yelling]

20:51.583 --> 20:52.517
[frogs croaking]

20:52.584 --> 20:54.319
- [exclaiming]

20:54.386 --> 20:57.189
You are the frog hero!

20:57.255 --> 20:58.724
[both sigh]

21:00.325 --> 21:01.793
- We're sorry, guys.

21:01.860 --> 21:03.528
We failed you.

21:03.595 --> 21:04.863
- If only Principal Huggins

21:04.930 --> 21:08.200
could see you the way we do.

21:08.266 --> 21:11.670
Hops! You beautiful,
green, warty genius!

21:11.737 --> 21:13.372
Up high, buddy.

21:13.438 --> 21:14.573
- [crying]

21:14.640 --> 21:16.541
That was the most
beautiful thing

21:16.608 --> 21:18.744
I've ever seen!

21:18.810 --> 21:21.313
[both sobbing]

21:21.380 --> 21:22.547
- Don't hog it, Huggins.

21:22.614 --> 21:24.683
I want to watch it again.

21:24.750 --> 21:27.386
{\an1}- See? Frogs are way cooler
on the outside.

21:27.452 --> 21:29.855
{\an3}- There is no way
we're dissecting them.

21:29.921 --> 21:32.290
{\an3}But what are we going to do
with all these frogs?

21:32.357 --> 21:33.692
- I'm glad you asked.

21:33.759 --> 21:36.895
[frogs croaking]

21:37.929 --> 21:40.198
{\an1}- We call it
the frog-ay fortress.

21:40.265 --> 21:41.667
- [gasping]
- Oh, that's awesome.

21:41.733 --> 21:42.934
[all exclaiming]

21:43.001 --> 21:45.337
- Um, what are
those two frogs doing?

21:45.404 --> 21:46.471
- [exclaims]

21:46.538 --> 21:48.774
Class dismissed!

21:48.840 --> 21:51.276
{\an1}- I'm sorry Principal Huggins
gave you detention.

21:51.343 --> 21:52.511
- That's okay.

21:52.577 --> 21:54.680
{\an3}All that matters is that
the frogs are safe

21:54.746 --> 21:56.848
{\an3}and things can go back
to normal.

21:58.216 --> 21:59.651
both: "Tonight's special:

21:59.718 --> 22:02.054
{\an8}roasted duck enchiladas"?

22:03.455 --> 22:05.957
[ducks quacking]

22:10.462 --> 22:11.930
{\an8}<i>- ♪ Cramped inside</i>
<i>this tiny space ♪</i>

22:11.997 --> 22:13.765
{\an8}<i>♪ May sound bad</i>
<i>but ain't the case ♪</i>

22:13.832 --> 22:16.702
{\an8}<i>♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>
<i>- ♪ Loud house ♪</i>

22:16.768 --> 22:19.171
{\an8}<i>- ♪ Duck and dodge</i>
<i>and push and shove ♪</i>

22:19.237 --> 22:23.241
{\an8}<i>♪ That's the way we show</i>
<i>our love in the Loud house ♪</i>

22:23.308 --> 22:24.609
{\an8}<i>- ♪ Loud house ♪</i>

22:24.676 --> 22:26.211
{\an8}<i>♪ Laundry piles</i>
<i>stacked up high ♪</i>

22:26.278 --> 22:27.379
{\an8}<i>♪ Hand-me-downs</i>
<i>that make me cry ♪</i>

22:27.446 --> 22:28.613
{\an8}<i>♪ Stand in line to take a pee ♪</i>

22:28.680 --> 22:30.048
{\an8}<i>♪ Never any privacy ♪</i>

22:30.115 --> 22:32.584
{\an8}<i>♪ Chaos with 11 kids ♪</i>

22:32.651 --> 22:35.120
{\an8}<i>♪ That's the way</i>
<i>it always is ♪</i>

22:35.187 --> 22:36.488
{\an8}<i>♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>
